{title: That Old Texas Two Step}
{artist: Charlie Walker}
{composer: Written by Harlan Howard and Ronald R. Peterson}

[C]Sign said country music and the [D7]parking lot was full
So I [G7]parked my truck and gave that southern comfort one more [C]pull
Then I walked into that Texas bar [D7]right away I saw
A girl that oughta be against the [G7]law
Her [C]smile said come on over so I [D7]grabbed a couple a-beers
And [G7]eased up to that fantasy I dreamed about for [C]years
Knew I was a goner when I [D7]looked into her eyes
